{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T09:00:13.091Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sandboxing agent code execution in Docker/gVisor is the practice of running Claude-powered agents inside "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"isolated execution environments"},{"type":"text","text":" so that the agent can execute arbitrary code, tools, or scripts without being able to harm your host system, leak secrets, or compromise other services. In "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Self-Hosted Agent Runtimes"},{"type":"text","text":", this means you build and manage the isolation yourself, unlike Managed Agents where Anthropic provides secure cloud sandboxes."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What it is"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sandboxing creates a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"security boundary"},{"type":"text","text":" between the agent and your infrastructure:\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Docker containers"},{"type":"text","text":": Provide OS-level isolation, resource limits, and network confinement for agent execution.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"gVisor"},{"type":"text","text":": A stricter sandbox that uses seccomp filters and minimal kernels to restrict what code can do, even inside containers.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Self-hosted sandboxes"},{"type":"text","text":": You control the infrastructure (unlike Anthropic-managed sandboxes), which is critical for compliance, data residency, or when you need custom tool execution."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The agent runs inside the sandbox and can execute tools, scripts, or LLM code generation, but the sandbox prevents it from escaping to the host or accessing unauthorized resources."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why it matters"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sandboxing is essential for production agent workloads because:\n- Agents can be triggered by "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"malicious prompts"},{"type":"text","text":" that try to execute harmful code or access secrets.\n- Without sandboxing, the agent could "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"read your filesystem"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"exfiltrate data"},{"type":"text","text":", or "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"compromise other services"},{"type":"text","text":".\n- Self-hosted sandboxes let you control "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"security boundaries"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"credential management"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"data residency"},{"type":"text","text":" requirements."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For enterprise deployments, sandboxing is one of the core security controls: it prevents the agent from executing arbitrary system commands, accessing sensitive files, or communicating with unauthorized networks."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mental model"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Think of the sandbox as a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"sealed room"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- The agent is inside the room.\n- The room has "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"limited tools"},{"type":"text","text":" (e.g., can read specific files, run specific commands).\n- The room has "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"no escape"},{"type":"text","text":" (cannot access the host filesystem or network).\n- The room has "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"resource limits"},{"type":"text","text":" (cannot consume infinite CPU/memory)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Docker provides the room's walls. gVisor adds an extra layer of security inside the room by restricting what the agent's code can actually do."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How it works"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Docker containerization"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Docker provides isolation through:\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Filesystem isolation"},{"type":"text","text":": Each container has its own filesystem, not shared with the host.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Network isolation"},{"type":"text","text":": Containers can have their own network stack or be restricted.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Resource limits"},{"type":"text","text":": CPU, memory, and disk quotas prevent resource exhaustion.\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Process isolation"},{"type":"text","text":": Containers run in separate process namespaces."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A typical agent Docker setup:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# docker-compose.yml\nversion: \"3.8\"\nservices:\n  agent-runner:\n    image: agent-runtime:latest\n    container_name: claude-agent\n    security_opt:\n      - no-new-privileges:true\n    read_only: true\n    tmpfs:\n      - /tmp\n    volumes:\n      - ./sandbox-data:/sandbox:ro\n    networks:\n      - agent-net\n    deploy:\n      resources:\n        limits:\n          cpus: \"2\"\n          memory: 4G"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This configuration:\n- Makes the container filesystem read-only (except "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"/tmp"},{"type":"text","text":").\n- Limits filesystem access to a specific sandbox directory.\n- Restricts network access to an internal network.\n- Limits CPU and memory resources."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"gVisor enforcement"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"gVisor adds "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"seccomp filters"},{"type":"text","text":" and a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"minimal kernel"},{"type":"text","text":" that restricts what code can execute inside the container:\n- Blocks dangerous system calls (e.g., "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"ptrace"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"mount"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"execve"},{"type":"text","text":").\n- Prevents the agent from escaping the container.\n- Adds an extra security layer beyond standard Docker isolation."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"gVisor is particularly useful when:\n- The agent executes "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"arbitrary code"},{"type":"text","text":" (e.g., code generation from LLM).\n- You need "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"stricter security"},{"type":"text","text":" than Docker provides alone.\n- You're running agents in "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"multi-tenant environments"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A gVisor profile might look like:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"json"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"seccomp\": {\n    \"defaultAction\": \"SCMP_ERR\",\n    \"syscalls\": [\n      {\n        \"names\": [\"read\", \"write\", \"exit\", \"exit_group\"],\n        \"action\": \"SCMP_ALLOW\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This blocks all system calls except the explicitly allowed ones."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Self-hosted vs. managed sandboxes"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Aspect"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Self-hosted (Docker/gVisor)"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Managed (Anthropic)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Control"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You control infrastructure, security, and data"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Anthropic controls infrastructure"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Compliance"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Can meet custom compliance requirements"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Limited to Anthropic's cert scope"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Data residency"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Can enforce data stays in your region"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Data may be processed by Anthropic"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Setup complexity"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Requires infrastructure engineering"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Turnkey, no setup"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Security"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You manage security boundaries"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Anthropic manages security"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Self-Hosted Agent Runtimes"},{"type":"text","text":", you build the sandbox yourself. For "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Managed Agents"},{"type":"text","text":", Anthropic provides secure cloud sandboxes with pre-installed packages and network access."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementation patterns"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Simple Docker sandbox"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For basic agent execution:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"bash"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"docker run \\\n  --rm \\\n  --name claude-agent \\\n  --read-only \\\n  --tmpfs /tmp:rw,noexec,nosuid,size=1G \\\n  --cap-drop ALL \\\n  --security-opt no-new-privileges:true \\\n  --user agent-user \\\n  agent-runtime:latest"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This:\n- Removes the container after exit ("},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"--rm"},{"type":"text","text":").\n- Makes the filesystem read-only.\n- Creates a temporary writable filesystem for "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"/tmp"},{"type":"text","text":".\n- Drops all capabilities (no privileged operations).\n- Removes user privileges.\n- Runs as a non-root user."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"gVisor-enforced sandbox"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For stricter security:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"bash"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"docker run \\\n  --runtime=gvisor \\\n  --rm \\\n  --name claude-agent Secure \\\n  agent-runtime:latest"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This uses gVisor as the container runtime, adding the extra security layer."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Security considerations"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Credential management"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Store credentials in "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"managed secret stores"},{"type":"text","text":" (e.g., Vault, AWS Secrets Manager), not in the container."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"short-lived credentials"},{"type":"text","text":" that expire automatically."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Rotate credentials"},{"type":"text","text":" regularly."}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Network isolation"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Restrict network access to "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"specific endpoints"},{"type":"text","text":" (e.g., only Anthropic's API)."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"firewall rules"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"network policies"},{"type":"text","text":" to block unauthorized connections."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Don't allow the agent to access your internal network unless explicitly needed."}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Filesystem restrictions"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Make the container filesystem "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"read-only"},{"type":"text","text":" except for specific directories."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"tmpfs"},{"type":"text","text":" for temporary writable storage."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Don't expose the host filesystem to the container."}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Resource limits"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Set "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"CPU and memory limits"},{"type":"text","text":" to prevent resource exhaustion."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"disk quotas"},{"type":"text","text":" to prevent disk exhaustion."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Monitor resource usage and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"alert on anomalies"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Trade-offs"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefits:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- You control "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"security boundaries"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"data residency"},{"type":"text","text":".\n- Can meet "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"custom compliance requirements"},{"type":"text","text":".\n- More "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"flexible"},{"type":"text","text":" for custom tool execution.\n- Lower latency for "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"local execution"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Trade-offs:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- You must "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"build and maintain"},{"type":"text","text":" the sandbox infrastructure.\n- More "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"complex"},{"type":"text","text":" than managed sandboxes.\n- Requires "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"infrastructure engineering"},{"type":"text","text":" expertise.\n- You're responsible for "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"security updates"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"monitoring"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Best practices"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Docker with read-only filesystems"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"tmpfs"},{"type":"text","text":" for writable storage."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Enable "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"gVisor"},{"type":"text","text":" for stricter security when executing arbitrary code."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Drop all capabilities"},{"type":"text","text":" and run as "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"non-root"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Set "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"resource limits"},{"type":"text","text":" (CPU, memory, disk)."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"managed secret stores"},{"type":"text","text":" for credentials."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Monitor"},{"type":"text","text":" sandbox health and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"alert on anomalies"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Rotate credentials"},{"type":"text","text":" regularly and use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"short-lived tokens"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key takeaways"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sandbox agent execution in "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Docker containers"},{"type":"text","text":" for OS-level isolation and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"gVisor"},{"type":"text","text":" for stricter security."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Self-hosted sandboxes let you control "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"security boundaries"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"data residency"},{"type":"text","text":", unlike managed sandboxes."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key security controls: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"read-only filesystems"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"tmpfs"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"capability drops"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"non-root users"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"resource limits"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"managed secret stores"},{"type":"text","text":" for credentials, not container environment variables."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sandbox isolation is critical for preventing "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"malicious code execution"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"data exfiltration"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"host compromise"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph"}]}}
